Analysis of the Target Image
----------------------------
• Overall Count and Layers  
  – There are 9 total blocks arranged into two separate “sub‐structures.”  
  – Left Sub‐Structure (4 blocks, stacked in three layers):  
     1) A yellow rectangular block on the very top.  
     2) Two red half‐circle blocks forming a circular “window” in the middle.  
     3) A yellow rectangular block on the bottom.  
  – Right Sub‐Structure (5 blocks, stacked in four layers):  
     1) Two orange cylindrical blocks side by side on the bottom.  
     2) A single green rectangular block bridging across those two cylinders.  
     3) A red cube stacked on top of that green block.  
     4) A blue cube on the very top.

• Spatial Relationships  
  – Left side: The two yellow blocks sandwich the red “ring” (made from two red halves).  
  – Right side: Two orange cylinders support a single green plank, which in turn supports a red cube, then finally the blue cube.

Required Blocks From the Dictionary
-----------------------------------
To match color/shape/orientation exactly (with no re‐orientation allowed), the following indices are used:

1) Red half‐circle (top half) … Block #4  
2) Red half‐circle (bottom half) … Block #5  
3) Blue cube … Block #6  
4) Red cube … Block #9  
5) Green rectangular block (horizontal) … Block #11  
6) Yellow rectangular block (horizontal) … Block #14 (used twice)  
7) Orange cylinder (horizontal) … Block #16 (used twice)  

Hence the needed list of dictionary indices is:  
• 4 × 1  
• 5 × 1  
• 6 × 1  
• 9 × 1  
• 11 × 1  
• 14 × 2  
• 16 × 2  

Step‐by‐Step Assembly Instructions
----------------------------------
{
  Step1: Move block with index 14  (place it as the bottom of the left sub‐structure)  
  Step2: Move block with index 5   (stack onto the yellow block to form the lower half of the red ring)  
  Step3: Move block with index 4   (stack above the previous red half to complete the circular opening)  
  Step4: Move block with index 14  (place on top to finish the left sub‐structure)  
  Step5: Move block with index 16  (first orange cylinder for the right sub‐structure’s base)  
  Step6: Move block with index 16  (second orange cylinder, side by side with the first)  
  Step7: Move block with index 11  (green rectangular plank bridging the two cylinders)  
  Step8: Move block with index 9   (red cube goes on top of the green plank)  
  Step9: Move block with index 6   (blue cube on top of the red cube)  
}
